title: Chris Evans, Lakeith Stanfield, and Michael Shannon Join Daniel Craig In Rian Johnson's Crime Thriller 'Knives Out' - GWW
excerpt: Writer-director Rian Johnson‘s crime thriller Knives Out starring Bond actor Daniel Craig is lining up an impressive supporting cast. Details currently on the film are a little scarce at the moment. Deadline reports that Lakeith Stanfield (Atlanta, Get Out, Girl In The Spider’s Web) will play a detective in the film alongside Daniel Craig’s character. Earlier they also revealed that Captain America actor Chris Evans would also have a role in the film, which now explains the delays on Neill Blomkamp’s Greenland which was had it’s production start pushed to the winter and possibly into next year. summary: So hypothetically speaking, if I just never watch Avengers 4  live in Fanfiction-land for the rest of my life  does that mean...
body:
So hypothetically speaking, if I just

  • never watch Avengers 4
  • live in Fanfiction-land for the rest of my life

does that mean that Steve Rogers lives forever, and Chris Evans never stops playing him?  Is that, like, Schrödinger’s Cap?
